I soooooo relate with you it's scarry. Let me start at the beginning. I was about 22yo married 2 kids working hard. A combination of bad choices and something unknown brought my mental illness to the forefront. Of course I was put on medication they figured I was just an alcoholic with major depression.  I stayed married throughout the 90s lost jobs from drinking and womanizing really reached a high point on my life. I went to AA various times through those years also lots of therapy. I never really questioned why was I the way I am. My doctor did wonder how I became so fucked up. I was asked countless times over those years if I was molested as a kid. Towards the end of the century I was unemployed couldn't afford my medication let alone therapy . I got hooked up with the county mental health system. Dam that was the best thing that ever happened. I got to see my therapist about every day so I had allot of talking things out getting emotions out. I was told that I had all the characteristics of someone who was molested as a child. I blamed my grandfather there were some memories very faint ones. I cried it was like someone opened a dam. After I accepted I was molested for some reason I was able to look past that hurdle and work on my mental state at that moment. I got a job as a janitor and worked my way into working for the county mental health department been there 19 years now. Ok about 2000 I had my insurance benefits so I started going to Kaiser. I'll cut to the chase I was diagnosed BPD. At that time there were not many men diagnosed with bpd. They were around but I seemed to feel alone like the only man in DBT class and group therapy. Nowadays I havent drank in about 19 years married I still get my old feelings to see other women. Sometimes I give in but right now under control. I go to therapy still and one question has came to mind many times. Was I really molested or did I just give in with the therapy and bleaved I was molested. My therapist had offered some kind of hypno treatment to find out the real truth. I dont really bleave that would help at this point in my life. 4 kids and I'm 52 years old now. Understand I spent many nights and days pondering  over the question if it happend or not. Finally I made the decision that it really dont matter anymore in my life. It's not going to change anything at all in my present life. So fuck it I'm Me I have BPD I dont question if I was or wasn't anymore. Let dead dogs lye kind of thing. What matters is the thought that I was molested allowed me to move on and work on fixing myself and doing DBT. I dont mean to make less of your situation.  I'm just grateful that I was able to get past the thought and start leading a somewhat good life and helping others.

The day full disclosure comes the world will never be the same again. Maybe people will actually be cool and accept the real truth. But more then likely religion will fall into a tailspin and it will case mass panic. When I was a kid I actually saw a real UFO. It had the lights and hovered and zipped around like a hummingbird.
